{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772114794,"nonce":"KFqruxjxmmfyCKNTFjna+DcuV0o=","title":"Searchkick lendings_count mapping missing — lending page crashes with 500","message":"The lending page (/ausleihe) returns 500 because Elasticsearch has no mapping for the `lendings_count` field on the ParentItem index. The Searchkick query tries to sort by `lendings_count` but ES rejects it:\n\n```\nNo mapping found for [lendings_count] in order to sort on\n```\n\nThis happens after a fresh `docker compose up -d` and reindex. The entrypoint reindexes ParentItem, but since there are no items with lendings in the seed data, ES never creates a mapping for `lendings_count`. When the lending controller queries with `sort: {lendings_count: :desc}`, ES fails.\n\nPossible fixes:\n- Add explicit mapping for `lendings_count` in the Searchkick config so it exists even with no data\n- Handle the missing mapping gracefully in the search query\n- Seed at least one item so the mapping gets created\n\nStack trace points to `app/models/parent_item.rb:62` → `ParentItem.search_items` → `LendingController#index`.","files":null}]}